com.ucguy4u.linkedlist

Class SinglyLinkList

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ucguy4u.linkedlist.SinglyLinkList

  • public class SinglyLinkList
extends Object
    A singly linked list is a type of linked list that is unidirectional, that is, it can be traversed in only one direction from head to the last node (tail). Each element in a linked list is called a node. A single node contains data and a pointer to the next node which helps in maintaining the structure of the list. Implementing Singly linked list

    uschauha
